{"id":10,"date":"2019-11-27T17:46:30","date_gmt":"2019-11-27T16:46:30","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.gotriple.eu\/?page_id=10"},"modified":"2023-03-07T08:18:18","modified_gmt":"2023-03-07T07:18:18","slug":"about","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/about\/","title":{"rendered":"About TRIPLE"},"content":{"rendered":"<div id=\"modal-ready\">\n<p id=\"Information-Material\"><strong><a href=\"#Funding-information\">Detailed Funding Information<\/a><\/strong><br><strong><a href=\"#Project-timeline\">Project Timeline<\/a><br><a href=\"#GOTRIPLE\">The GoTriple Platform<\/a><br><a href=\"#Aims\">Goals and Impacts<\/a><\/strong><br><strong><a href=\"#Governance\">Governance<\/a><\/strong><br><a href=\"#Work-Packages\" data-type=\"internal\"><strong>Work Packages<\/strong><\/a><br><a href=\"#TRIPLE-in-the-EOSC\" data-type=\"internal\" data-id=\"#TRIPLE-in-the-EOSC\"><strong>TRIPLE in the EOSC<\/strong><\/a><br><strong><a href=\"#Information-Materials\" data-type=\"internal\" data-id=\"#Information-Materials\">Information Material<\/a><\/strong><br><\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-text-color has-css-opacity has-background is-style-wide\" style=\"background-color:#622166;color:#622166\"\/>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/www.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TRIPLE_LOGO-Title1-1024x391.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-63\" width=\"482\" height=\"184\" srcset=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TRIPLE_LOGO-Title1-1024x391.png 1024w, https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TRIPLE_LOGO-Title1-300x115.png 300w, https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TRIPLE_LOGO-Title1-768x293.png 768w, https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/TRIPLE_LOGO-Title1.png 1150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 482px) 100vw, 482px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The TRIPLE project was launched in October 2019. The acronym TRIPLE stands for &#8220;Transforming Research through Innovative Practices for Linked Interdisciplinary Exploration&#8221;. TRIPLE consists of a <a href=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/partners\/\">consortium of 22 partners<\/a> from 15 European countries and is coordinated from France by the Research Infrastructure\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/www.huma-num.fr\/\">Huma-Num<\/a>, a unit of the\u00a0<a href=\"http:\/\/www.cnrs.fr\/en\">French National Centre for Scientific Research (CNRS)<\/a>. Project and scientific coordinator is <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/operas.hypotheses.org\/4147\" target=\"_blank\">Suzanne Dumouchel<\/a>, who is also Co-coordinator of <a href=\"https:\/\/operas-eu.org\">OPERAS<\/a> and Member of the Board of Directors of the EOSC Association. She is supported by the TRIPLE team with currently around 90 staff members working in one or more of the\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/work-packages\/\">8 work packages<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>At the heart of the project is the development of the <strong><a href=\"#GOTRIPLE\">GoTriple platform<\/a><\/strong>, an innovative multilingual and multicultural discovery solution. It will be one of the dedicated services of <a href=\"https:\/\/operas-eu.org\">OPERAS<\/a>, the Research Infrastructure supporting open scholarly communication in the social sciences and humanities (SSH) in the <a href=\"https:\/\/ec.europa.eu\/info\/research-and-innovation\/strategy\/era_en\">European Research Area<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image is-resized\"><a href=\"https:\/\/operas-eu.org\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/www.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/Logo-OPERAS-new-Title-e1575292094536-300x74.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-64\" width=\"111\" height=\"27\" srcset=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/Logo-OPERAS-new-Title-e1575292094536-300x74.png 300w, https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/11\/Logo-OPERAS-new-Title-e1575292094536.png 680w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 111px) 100vw, 111px\" \/><\/a><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"Funding-information\">Detailed Funding Information<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The TRIPLE project is financed under the <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/ec.europa.eu\/programmes\/horizon2020\/what-horizon-2020\" target=\"_blank\">Horizon 2020<\/a> Framework Programme with approx. 5.6 million Euros for a duration of 42 months (2019-2023).<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><em>H2020 parent programme<\/em>: <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/cordis.europa.eu\/programme\/id\/H2020-EU.1.4.1.\" target=\"_blank\">\u201cDeveloping the European research infrastructures for 2020 and beyond\u201d<\/a> <\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><em>Programme<\/em>: <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/cordis.europa.eu\/programme\/id\/H2020-EU.1.4.1.3.\" target=\"_blank\">H2020-EU.1.4.1.3. \u2013 \u201cDevelopment, deployment and operation of ICT-based e-infrastructures\u201d<\/a> <\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><em>Topic<\/em>: <a href=\"https:\/\/eosc-portal.eu\/infraeosc-02-2019-prototyping-new-innovative-services\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">INFRAEOSC-02-2019 \u201cPrototyping new innovative services\u201d<\/a>\n<ul>\n<li>Funding scheme: RIA &#8211; Research and Innovation action<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Grant agreement number: 863420<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><em>Call for proposal<\/em>: H2020-INFRAEOSC-2019-1<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You can find official EU information on the TRIPLE project on the <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/cordis.europa.eu\/about\/en\" target=\"_blank\">Community Research and Development Information Service (CORDIS)<\/a> platform, the European Commission&#8217;s primary source of results from the projects funded by the EU&#8217;s framework programmes for Research and Innovation: <a href=\"https:\/\/cordis.europa.eu\/project\/id\/863420\">https:\/\/cordis.europa.eu\/project\/id\/863420<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"Project-timeline\">Project Timeline<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"853\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/TRIPLE_dpTIMELine_2021_WEBSITE_1000X_FINAL-Update-853x1024.png\" alt=\"TRIPLE Project Timeline\" class=\"wp-image-1209\" srcset=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/TRIPLE_dpTIMELine_2021_WEBSITE_1000X_FINAL-Update-853x1024.png 853w, https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/TRIPLE_dpTIMELine_2021_WEBSITE_1000X_FINAL-Update-250x300.png 250w, https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/TRIPLE_dpTIMELine_2021_WEBSITE_1000X_FINAL-Update-768x922.png 768w, https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/TRIPLE_dpTIMELine_2021_WEBSITE_1000X_FINAL-Update-1280x1536.png 1280w, https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/TRIPLE_dpTIMELine_2021_WEBSITE_1000X_FINAL-Update-1707x2048.png 1707w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 853px) 100vw, 853px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">TRIPLE Project Timeline (2019-2023) (designed by EKT)<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"GOTRIPLE\">The GoTriple Platform<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Inspired by the <a href=\"https:\/\/isidore.science\">Isidore search engine<\/a> developed by the <a href=\"http:\/\/www.cnrs.fr\/en\">French National Centre for Scientific Research (CNRS)<\/a>, the <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.gotriple.eu\/\" target=\"_blank\">GoTriple platform<\/a> provides a central access point for users (researchers, institutions such as universities and libraries, but also enterprises, consultancies, media and service providers)<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>to discover and reuse open scholarly SSH resources, i.e. research data and publications, which are currently scattered across local repositories;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>to find and connect with other researchers and projects across disciplinary and language boundaries;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>to make use of innovative tools to support research (e.g. visualisation, annotation, trust building and recommender system);<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>to discover new ways of funding research (e.g. crowdfunding).<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Find more information here: <a href=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/gotriple-platform\/\">https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/gotriple-platform\/<\/a>. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The GoTriple platform is accessible via the link <a href=\"https:\/\/gotriple.eu\/\">https:\/\/gotriple.eu\/<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"Aims\">Goals and Impacts<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>TRIPLE supports SSH research in Europe<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>to\ngain visibility;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>to\nbe more efficient and effective;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>to\nimprove its reuse within the SSH and beyond;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>to\nsignificantly increase the economic and societal impact of SSH resources.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>TRIPLE <\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>imagines\nnew ways to conduct, connect and discover research;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>facilitates\ninterdisciplinary projects and large-scale scientific collaborations;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>supports\nscientific, industrial and societal applications of SSH science;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>promotes\ncultural and linguistic diversity within Europe;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>connects\nresearchers and projects with other stakeholders: citizens, policy makers,\ncompanies, enabling them to take part in joint research projects and to address\nsome of their issues.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The project\u2019s final goal is to integrate the discovery solution, which will be fully operationable by 2023, into the <a href=\"https:\/\/marketplace.eosc-portal.eu\/\">EOSC marketplace<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-1 wp-block-gallery aligncenter has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"900\" height=\"720\" data-id=\"1244\"  src=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/TRIPLE-Main-goals.png\" alt=\"TRIPLE main goals\" class=\"wp-image-1244\" srcset=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/TRIPLE-Main-goals.png 900w, https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/TRIPLE-Main-goals-300x240.png 300w, https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/TRIPLE-Main-goals-768x614.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"898\" height=\"718\" data-id=\"1243\"  src=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/TRIPLE-Main-impacts.png\" alt=\"TRIPLE main impacts\" class=\"wp-image-1243\" srcset=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/TRIPLE-Main-impacts.png 898w, https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/TRIPLE-Main-impacts-300x240.png 300w, https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/TRIPLE-Main-impacts-768x614.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 898px) 100vw, 898px\" \/><\/figure>\n<\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"Governance\">Governance<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>For information about the TRIPLE governance, click here: <a href=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/governance\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/governance\/<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"Work-Packages\">Work Packages<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>For information about the TRIPLE work packages, click here: <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/work-packages\/\" target=\"_blank\">https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/work-packages\/<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"TRIPLE-in-the-EOSC\">TRIPLE in the EOSC<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>For information about TRIPLE in the EOSC, click here: <a href=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/triple-in-the-eosc\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/triple-in-the-eosc\/<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"Information-Materials\">Information Material<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>For information material about the TRIPLE project such as leaflets, TRIPLE logo &amp; symbol and document templates, click here: <a href=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/information-material\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/information-material\/<\/a><\/p>\n<\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Detailed Funding InformationProject TimelineThe GoTriple PlatformGoals and ImpactsGovernanceWork PackagesTRIPLE in the EOSCInformation Material The TRIPLE project was launched in October 2019. The acronym TRIPLE stands for &#8220;Transforming Research through Innovative Practices for Linked Interdisciplinary Exploration&#8221;. TRIPLE consists of a consortium<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":3,"featured_media":61,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/10"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp